  I'm sorry that I haven't done this sooner, but here are some guidelines for membership into Ben Order.  These are to keep the lvl of member up and still give us the ablity to grow... so without further ado...<br>
<br>
Rules:<br>
 1. All new applicants must have at least one full member (any member of Ben Order that has been playing in the guild for 3 weeks or more)vouch for them before being allowed to join.  The full member is to /tell an officer (preferably me - its my job y'all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and then give a BRIEF testimony as to why this new applicant be allowed in.<br>
<br>
 2. Once the new member is invited, he/she/it will be on probation until he has played for no less than 3 weeks.  The only exception to this is RL friends which I will get into below.  This prohibitory period is to make sure that this player will be a good fit for Ben Order and that they will in fact play enough to be a good guildmate.  During this period they cannot vouch for other applicants, this being to keep from new members railroading a bunch of their cronies into the guild.  Again see the exception for RL friends.  If a new member asks how his friend(s) (some of us have more than one friend...) can join the guild, tell em that they need to group with a full member.<br>
<br>
3. RL friends of full members will be allowed into the guild without hassle (except that which Khoal devises for all new members.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   see below).  RL members will assume full membership in Ben Order.  This is because you know that person really well (at least I hope so if you know em in RL).  They have all the rights of full members.  <br>
<br>
4. The only testing of the new members is a new member quest or perhaps a one time invitation fee.  Khoal, I want you to come up with a newbie quest that they can do for &quot;intiation.&quot;  The fee would only work if we have regular guild dues (I think that's a good thing, money for the guild for events and whatnot).  Otherwise, we'll only have the quest.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions over these, or feel like we need more rules (serious ones only hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )add em below... I hope this helps in your recruiting.  Good luck all and I'll see you in game!<br>
<br>
Sincerely, <p>Mathusis Furyblade

Ranger of Tunare
